{
  "id": "so-2003505-delete-git-branch",
  "category": "case-study",
  "source_url": "https://stackoverflow.com/questions/2003505/how-do-i-delete-a-git-branch-locally-and-remotely",
  "title": "How do I delete a Git branch locally and remotely?",
  "prompt": "I want to delete a branch both locally and remotely.\n\n```\n$ git branch -d the_local_branch\nerror: The branch 'the_local_branch' is not fully merged.\nIf you are sure you want to delete it, run 'git branch -D the_local_branch'.\n\n$ git push origin :the_remote_branch\nerror: unable to push to unqualified destination: the_remote_branch\n```\n\nWhat am I doing wrong, and what's the correct way to delete a branch both locally and from `origin`?",
  "assertion": {
    "kind": "all-of",
    "assertions": [
      {
        "kind": "any-of",
        "assertions": [
          { "kind": "regex", "pattern": "git\\s+branch\\s+-d\\b", "flags": "" },
          { "kind": "regex", "pattern": "git\\s+branch\\s+-D\\b", "flags": "" }
        ]
      },
      {
        "kind": "any-of",
        "assertions": [
          { "kind": "regex", "pattern": "git\\s+push\\s+(--delete|-d|origin\\s+--delete)", "flags": "i" },
          { "kind": "regex", "pattern": "git\\s+push\\s+origin\\s+(--delete|:[a-zA-Z_-])", "flags": "" }
        ]
      },
      {
        "kind": "any-of",
        "assertions": [
          { "kind": "regex", "pattern": "(unmerged|not\\s+fully\\s+merged|force(\\s+|-)?delete|capital\\s+d|-D\\s+(forces|forces?\\s+the\\s+delete))", "flags": "i" },
          { "kind": "regex", "pattern": "fetch\\s+--prune|git\\s+remote\\s+prune", "flags": "i" }
        ]
      }
    ]
  },
  "budget": { "maxTokens": 3000, "maxCostUsd": 0.04, "maxDurationSec": 60, "maxToolCalls": 2 }
}
